  "prompt": "Typically how many clients do massage spas serve per month at an average sized location?",
  "response": "The number of clients a massage spa serves per month can vary widely based on several factors including the location, size, services offered, pricing, and overall demand. However, an average-sized massage spa might see anywhere from 300 to 1,000 clients per month. \n\nFor a more detailed breakdown:\n\n- **Small Spa (2-3 therapists)**: May serve around 200-500 clients per month.\n- **Medium Spa (4-6 therapists)**: Can typically handle 500-1,000 clients per month.\n- **Large Spa (7+ therapists)**: Might exceed more than 1,000 clients, depending on the demand and operational hours.\n\nThese numbers can fluctuate based on seasonal trends, promotions, and the effectiveness of marketing strategies.",
